UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Improved and equitable access to and completion of quality, inclusive basic education with a focus on improving learning outcomes

description.narrative: Over 30,000 out of school children and adolescents benefitted from education and skills provided through formal and alternative modes of delivery with support from UNICEF, contributing to the reduction of out of school children in Tanzania from 3.5 million children in 2016 to 3.2 million children in 2021. Additionally, the national inclusive education strategy (2021-2026) is now available, and responds to demand, supply and enabling factors that keep children and adolescents out of school. | Status:Met | As-of Date:20/12/2021
